    <note type="dates"><date>1802–63</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish gardener. An expert on bedding schemes and hybridisation. Trained in the gardens at Beaufort Castle, Inverness-shire. Gardener to William Gordon-Cumming at his estate in Altyre, at the Dickson &amp; Turnbull nursery in Perth, and at the Caledonian Horticultural Society in Edinburgh. Head gardener and estate manager to William Gordon of Haffield House, Herefordshire, 1829–37; gardener to Thomas Harris of Kingsbury, Kilburn, London, then head gardener to William Fowle Middleton of Shrubland Park, Suffolk, from 1840. A regular contributor to the <hi rend="italic">Gardener’s Magazine</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Cottage Gardener.</hi></p></note>
    <note type="sources">
